totalAnswer: The buildings that have been the tallest in Portland, Oregon between 1927 and 1965 are the Public Service Building and the Hilton Portland Hotel. On the other hand, the Hilton Portland Hotel, now known as the Hilton Portland Downtown, became the tallest building in Oregon when it was finished in 1963 until 1972, standing at 23 floors and 295 feet tall, and it remained the tallest hotel in the city until the completion of the 546-foot tall Nines Hotel in 2008, and after a significant renovation in 2017, the building now hosts 455 guest rooms and a new restaurant.

The Public Service Building was built in 1927 and has a height of 220 feet with 16 floors. The Hilton Portland Hotel was constructed in 1963 and is 241 feet tall with 22 floors. Following the construction of this hotel, in 1965 the Harrison West Condominium Tower was created measuring at 256 feet tall with 25 floors.
